SIMPLE: courier
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Courier
<hw>Cou"ri*er</hw> <pr>(k??"r?-?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>courrier</ets>, fr. <ets>courre</ets>, <ets>courir</ets>, to run,
L. <ets>currere</ets>. See <er>Course</er>, <er>Current</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A messenger sent with haste to convey letters or
dispatches, usually on public business.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The wary Bassa . . . by speedy <qex>couriers</qex>, advertised
Solyman of the enemy's purpose.</q> <rj><qau>Knolles.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An attendant on travelers, whose business it is to
make arrangements for their convenience at hotels and on the
way.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Courlan</ent>⟦br⟧
